The paper focuses on visual communication and the use of a computational model to understand how humans use visual abstraction and pragmatic inference to communicate effectively. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of a deep convolutional neural network and probabilistic program suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also discusses the role of language and social cognition in visual communication, which suggests that it may also belong to the natural language processing (cs.CL) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-categories.
